  <h1>AI Automation in Switzerland – A Guide for SMEs &amp; Freelancers</h1>

  <p class="intro">AI automation is no longer just for large corporations. Swiss SMEs, agencies and freelancers are saving hours every day – without an IT department, without coding skills. This guide explains what's worth automating, what it costs, and how to get started.</p>

  <h2>What Is AI Automation? (and what it isn't)</h2>
  <p>AI automation means: digital tasks that a person currently handles manually are taken over by an AI system. This goes beyond macros or simple scripts – AI understands context, recognises patterns and can handle unstructured data like emails, PDFs and forms.</p>
  <p><strong>Typical examples:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Classify, prioritise emails and generate draft replies</li>
    <li>Generate proposals from briefing notes</li>
    <li>Automatically compile weekly reports from multiple tools</li>
    <li>Create and send invoices (e.g. from Toggl time tracking)</li>
    <li>Summarise documents and PDFs</li>
    <li>Automate internal processes like onboarding or data maintenance</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>What AI automation is not:</strong> a magic wand for unclear processes. The task needs to be describable – then it can be automated.</p>

  <h2>Which Processes Are Worth Automating?</h2>
  <p>Not every process is a good candidate. These three rules help you decide:</p>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Rule 1 – Does the process repeat daily or weekly?</h3>
    <p>The more often a process occurs, the greater the leverage. Processing emails: daily. Annual report: once a year – probably not worth it.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Rule 2 – Does it cost more than 2 hours per week per person?</h3>
    <p>Under 2 hours rarely makes sense. Between 2–10 hours is the sweet spot for automations with a clear ROI.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Rule 3 – Are there clearly defined inputs and outputs?</h3>
    <p>Input: email arrives. Output: classified + draft reply. The clearer the pattern, the easier the automation.</p>
  </div>
  <p><strong>10 typical candidates in Swiss SMEs:</strong></p>
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Email triage and draft replies</li>
    <li>Creating proposals and quotes</li>
    <li>Reporting (weekly/monthly)</li>
    <li>Invoicing and bookkeeping preparation</li>
    <li>Research and summaries</li>
    <li>Scheduling and calendar management</li>
    <li>CRM data maintenance</li>
    <li>Data transfer between tools (e.g. JIRA → Sheets)</li>
    <li>Social media content creation</li>
    <li>Onboarding processes and checklists</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI Automation vs. Traditional Software – The Difference</h2>
  <table class="compare-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Criterion</th><th>Traditional Software / Macros</th><th>AI Automation</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Handles structured data</td><td class="tick">✓</td><td class="tick">✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Handles emails, PDFs, free text</td><td class="cross">✗</td><td class="tick">✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Understands context and meaning</td><td class="cross">✗</td><td class="tick">✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Works with variable inputs</td><td class="cross">✗</td><td class="tick">✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>No coding needed for variants</td><td class="cross">✗</td><td class="tick">✓</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Cheaper for simple, stable processes</td><td class="tick">✓</td><td class="cross">–</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>Rule of thumb: if the process is always identical and just moves numbers, a macro is enough. As soon as language, documents or variability come into play, you need AI.</p>

  <h2>What Does AI Automation Cost in Switzerland?</h2>
  <p>Costs depend on complexity and scope. Typical ranges:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Single automation (e.g. email triage):</strong> CHF 1,500–4,000 one-time</li>
    <li><strong>Combination of 3–5 processes:</strong> CHF 5,000–15,000</li>
    <li><strong>Ongoing support / subscription:</strong> CHF 300–800/month</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="roi-box">
    <h3>ROI Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>3 employees each save 5 hours per week</p>
    <p>Internal hourly rate: CHF 80/h</p>
    <p>Savings: 3 × 5h × 48 weeks × CHF 80</p>
    <div class="roi-total">= CHF 57,600 / year</div>
    <p style="margin-top:.5rem;font-size:.85rem">At project costs of CHF 8,000, ROI is reached after ~7 weeks.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Common Mistakes When Getting Started</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Starting too big:</strong> Trying to automate everything at once leads to paralysis. Better: pick one use case, go live fast, build trust.</li>
    <li><strong>Wrong tool for the job:</strong> Not every AI solution fits every process. An analysis before building saves time and money.</li>
    <li><strong>No internal ownership:</strong> Automations need a responsible person internally – not for the code, but for maintenance and development.</li>
    <li><strong>Ignoring data protection:</strong> Swiss companies are subject to the nDSG. We build exclusively privacy-compliant solutions – no vendor lock-in, no uncontrolled data sharing.</li>
  </ul>

